<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3–2349: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-30T19:00:00-05:00">March 30,
                                1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>410. Emb authorized reply Premier’s request (Embtel 629, Mar 23) in sense
                        first two substantive paras Embtel 637 Mar 23. Regarding proposals last two
                        paras, no encouragement should be given Chinese such use remaining ECA funds
                        if reauthorized by Congress.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>